<DIV3 TYPE="recipe">
<HEAD>For an old Cough.</HEAD>
<P>Take Elicampane roots and boil them ten|der, then pound it in a wooden mortar, then rub it in through an hair sieve, then take clari|f<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">d hony, and lay a course in the bottom of a stean then a course of sliced wardens, then a course of the Elicampane and so again as long as you please; And then put the stean into a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> oven and bake them two or three hours, then take it two or three times a day, a spoonful at a time&punc;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="recipe">
<HEAD>Another for a Cough with a rheum.</HEAD>
<P>Take Brown sugar candy and put it pound|ed into a calves bladder, and lay it in spring water 24 hours, then cut the bladder and eat t with a Liquerish stick as the Cough doth trouble you.</P>
</DIV3>
