<DIV3 TYPE="recipe">
<HEAD>A Soveraign Medicine for a sore brest.</HEAD>
<P>Take a pottle of smiths water, the elder it is the better, if it smell a little, so much the bet|ter, also you must take a quarter of a pound of old alume, and white salt asmuch as ye can hold on the two fingers from the second joynt forth, two handfuls of Sage, two Heads of housleek put all these into the water and seethe it till it come to a quart, then let it stand with the Herbs in it, and wash the sor<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> breast well with the Herbs, and the wate<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> twice a day, and at every time ye wash it lay upon the sore, or sores, green Sage leaves till it be whole, this hath been proved and h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">aled a breast so sore as it was thought uncu|rable.</P>
<P><PB N="57" REF="36">Ye must warm the water and Herb<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> every <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ime ye dress the brest.</P>
