<P>Take Mallows as ye get to be holden in a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">harger, and cut them small, and seethe them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n a Gallon of running water, and when they <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">esodden soft, put thereto a potile of the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ro<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nds <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f Ale, and a quart of white wine, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd two penny white loaves, cutting off the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rusts leavened, make it thick, and put into it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">eers Sue<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, or Sheeps Sue<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, and lay it upon a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lew cloth or linen cloth, and lay it warm to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">he sore brest every day as long as its sore, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd it shall be healed by the grace of God.</P>
