<P>Take the lungs of a Fox dryed, the juice of Liquerice, Maidenhair, Fennel-seed, of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ach <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> like four ounces, make it in Sugar sodden in water as much as will suffice, some make it with the juice of Myrts, and then it is com|fortable for the stomack, this is a present re|medy for a Consumption.</P>
