<P>Take a handful of Rosemary tops, a handful of red Sage, a handful of Horehound, a hand|ful of Plantaine leaves, a handful of Hyssope, a handful of winter Savory, a pint of English hony, a pint of runing water, half a pound of blew Figs, half a pound of Raisins of the Sun, a stick of Liquerice, boil all these in a new pipkin, with a cover to it, cut them small, and put them into the pipkin, and let it boil softly un<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">il it be half consumed, then take and strain it through a cloth very well, then give the party four spoonfuls morning and evening.</P>
