<DIV3 TYPE="recipe">
<HEAD>For them that swound or are faint-hearted.</HEAD>
<P>Take Rosemary, Sage, Betony, and Marje|rom of each an handful, seethe them in a gallo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> of fair water till a quart be consumed, the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> take away the herbs, and put to the said wate<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> a pinte of good hony, then scum it well, the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> put in an ounce of Staechades tied in a fair linnen cloth, Let it seethe a little, then tak<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> out the Staechades, and add an ounce of Cinna|mon, three quarters of an ounce of Nut|meggs, and asmuch in Ginger in powder, drink it warm thrice every day six or seven dayes, <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">|fiet</HI>:</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="recipe">
