<DIV3 TYPE="recipe">
<HEAD>To make water of Rosemary.</HEAD>
<P>Take Rosemary flowers and in the midst of May ere the sun arise in the morning, take the Rosemary and strip the Leaves from the stalks and take four or five great roots of Elecam|pane and an handful or two of Sage and beat the Rosemary the roots and Sage together in a stone mortar till they be very small, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n take it up and take three ounces of Cubebs and half a pound of Anniseeds and beat the spices in a mortar of brasse every spice by it self, then take all the Herbs and all the spices and put them in four or six gallons of white wine, then put all these spices herbs and wine in an earthen pot and stop the pot close so that no air come thereto with a cover, made of earth, and set the same pot in the ground by the space of fifteen dayes, then take it and still it in a stillatory of tin otherwise called a Limbeck with a soft fire.</P>
